# Comment Policy

See docs/COMMENTS.md for the full policy.

## Write comments ONLY for:
- Non-obvious intent or "why" (never "what")
- Architecture decisions
- Security constraints
- Platform quirks or workarounds
- Performance tradeoffs
- Public API documentation (/// doc comments)

## NEVER write:
- Obvious comments ("// increment counter")
- Section dividers ("// ---- Methods ----")
- Commented-out code (delete it, use git)
- TODOs without a ticket/issue reference
- Implementation narration
